WEBVTT

00:05.873 --> 00:09.710 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening. I'm
Judy Woodruff. Gwen Ifill is
away.

00:09.710 --> 00:15.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight: The
World Health Organization
announces the Zika virus is
spreading

00:15.148 --> 00:22.189 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
explosively in the Americas,
predicting up to four million
people infected this year.

00:22.189 --> 00:26.326 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Also ahead this Thursday, we sit
down with Matthew Trevithick,
one of the Americans released

00:26.326 --> 00:29.196 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
this month from an
Iranian prison.

00:29.196 --> 00:30.931 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATTHEW TREVITHICK, Freed From
Iranian Prison: And he says, "Do
you know who Jason Rezaian

00:30.931 --> 00:32.566 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
is?"

00:32.566 --> 00:37.304 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I said, "Of course. The whole
world knows that name." And he
said, next sentence, "He's

00:37.304 --> 00:40.007 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
never leaving, and
neither are you."

00:40.007 --> 00:45.545 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And the politics
of corn, how ethanol plays a
vital role in Iowa.

00:45.545 --> 00:49.416 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID YEPSEN, Southern Illinois
University: Every member of the
United States Senate who

00:49.416 --> 00:54.054 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
has run comes through Iowa and
offers up an ethanol program.
Everyone has to worship at

00:54.054 --> 00:55.856 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the altar of ethanol.

00:55.856 --> 00:58.859 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

00:58.859 --> 01:04.665 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:04.665 --> 01:17.711 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: United Nations
health experts issued a powerful
new warning today about

01:17.711 --> 01:22.182 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Zika virus. The World Health
Organization said it may have
mushroomed into a full-blown

01:22.182 --> 01:24.785 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
global emergency.

01:24.785 --> 01:28.488 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. MARGARET CHAN, Director
General, World Health
Organization: It is now
spreading explosively.

01:28.488 --> 01:34.428 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The sense of
urgency was palpable as WHO
Director Margaret Chan addressed
a

01:34.428 --> 01:38.432 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
special session on the
Zika virus in Geneva.

01:38.432 --> 01:44.571 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. MARGARET CHAN: As of today,
cases have been reported in 23
countries and territories

01:44.571 --> 01:49.810 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in the region. The level of
alarm is extremely high.

01:49.810 --> 01:54.915 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Most of the
outbreak has been concentrated
across Central and South
America.

01:54.915 --> 02:00.621 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WHO officials estimated today
there could be three to four
million cases in the Americas

02:00.621 --> 02:04.491 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
over the next year alone.

02:04.491 --> 02:09.896 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Brazil, hosting this summer's
Olympics, has been hit the
hardest, with more than a
million

02:09.896 --> 02:16.470 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
people contracting the virus.
Fear has spiked there with a
rise in birth defects apparently

02:16.470 --> 02:22.776 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
caused by Zika, babies born with
small heads, known as
microcephaly, and with
neurological

02:22.776 --> 02:24.277 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
problems.

02:24.277 --> 02:30.450 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. MARGARET CHAN: The possible
links, only recently suspected,
have rapidly changed the

02:30.450 --> 02:36.590 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
risk profile of Zika from a mild
threat to one of alarming
proportions.

02:36.590 --> 02:42.396 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Researchers say
it's still relatively rare that
a pregnant woman infected

02:42.396 --> 02:48.568 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
around the time of delivery can
pass the virus to her newborn.
There's also been one report

02:48.568 --> 02:54.875 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of a possible spread through
blood transfusion, and another
through sexual contact.

02:54.875 --> 03:00.614 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, Brazil's President Dilma
Rousseff announced a meeting of
Latin American and Caribbean

03:00.614 --> 03:08.655 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
nations next week on how to
eradicate the virus. In the
meantime, some 220,000 Brazilian

03:08.655 --> 03:14.327 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
soldiers are going house to
house, checking for stagnant
water and fumigating for
mosquitoes

03:14.327 --> 03:17.364 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that transmit Zika.

03:17.364 --> 03:24.504 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
El Salvador has taken still more
drastic measures. Last week, its
deputy health minister urged

03:24.504 --> 03:31.745 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
women to refrain from getting
pregnant before 2018. At least
31 Americans were infected

03:31.745 --> 03:35.582 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the past year, but all are
believed to have contracted the
virus after traveling

03:35.582 --> 03:38.718 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to affected areas.

03:38.718 --> 03:45.192 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For now, there is no cure, and
the WHO says it could take years
to get a vaccine.

03:45.192 --> 03:51.131 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. SYLVAIN ALDIGHIERI, World
Health Organization: There is no
immunity. So we would expect
huge

03:51.131 --> 03:56.203 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
numbers of infections, some
detected, some not detected.

03:56.203 --> 04:01.808 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The agency was
criticized for not moving
quickly enough on the Ebola
outbreak.

04:01.808 --> 04:06.246 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But it's calling a crisis
meeting for Monday on whether to
declare Zika an international

04:06.246 --> 04:08.682 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
health emergency.

04:08.682 --> 04:14.554 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We will get an expert
perspective on Zika after the
news summary.

04:14.554 --> 04:19.826 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
An armed militia group is down
to its last four holdouts at a
wildlife refuge in Eastern

04:19.826 --> 04:25.799 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Oregon. Three more surrendered
overnight, a day after seven
were arrested and one was

04:25.799 --> 04:30.570 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
killed in a shoot-out. Their
jailed leader, Ammon Bundy, is
now urging the rest to -- quote

04:30.570 --> 04:32.506 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
-- "stand down and go home."

04:32.506 --> 04:35.542 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
His lawyer read a statement
from Bundy today.

04:35.542 --> 04:42.849 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISSA CASEY, Attorney for Ammon
Bundy: Turn yourselves in. Do
not use physical force.

04:42.849 --> 04:49.289 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Use the national platform that
we have to continue to defend
liberty through our
constitutional

04:49.289 --> 04:55.328 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
right in an Article 3 court
with an Article 3 judge.

04:55.328 --> 05:00.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In a YouTube
video posted today, one of the
remaining militia members said

05:00.567 --> 05:07.207 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they're willing to depart the
refuge, if police promise they
won't be arrested.

05:07.207 --> 05:12.946 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Dangerous winter sea crossings
to Europe turned deadly again
today. At least 25 migrants
drowned

05:12.946 --> 05:17.918 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
when their boat sank off the
Greek island of Samos en route
from Turkey. Meanwhile,

05:17.918 --> 05:25.091 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Italian navy rescued nearly
300 people, and recovered six
bodies off Sicily.

05:25.091 --> 05:30.964 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Pentagon has announced it's
doubling paid maternity leave to
12 weeks for women in uniform

05:30.964 --> 05:35.635 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and military child care centers
will stay open longer.

05:35.635 --> 05:39.339 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Defense Secretary Ash Carter
said it's part of an effort to
recruit and retain a top-flight

05:39.339 --> 05:40.907 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
military.

05:40.907 --> 05:44.544 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ASHTON CARTER, U.S. Defense
Secretary: We will become a more
powerful magnet for the

05:44.544 --> 05:48.949 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
high-end talent we will need in
the coming generation. We will
make it easier to retain

05:48.949 --> 05:53.553 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the top talent we have and
to develop future leaders.

05:53.553 --> 05:59.593 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Carter also
called for greater health care
benefits for military women.

05:59.593 --> 06:04.598 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NASA today marked the 30th
anniversary of the Challenger
disaster. Six astronauts and

06:04.598 --> 06:11.905 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a teacher were killed on January
28, 1986, when a booster
exploded and blew the shuttle

06:11.905 --> 06:16.610 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
apart. The crew of the
International Space Station
observed a moment of silence
today,

06:16.610 --> 06:21.047 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and a ceremony at Cape Canaveral
honored the men and women of
Challenger.

06:21.047 --> 06:26.019 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BOB CABANA, Director, Kennedy
Space Center: They continue to
motivate us to explore and

06:26.019 --> 06:32.959 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to never quit just because it's
hard. We are better for having
known them. They are a part

06:32.959 --> 06:36.696 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of us forever and we will
never let them down.

06:36.696 --> 06:41.801 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We will take a
longer look at the Challenger
later in the program.

06:41.801 --> 06:46.740 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A former Providence, Rhode
Island, mayor who became a
larger-than-life figure has
died.

06:46.740 --> 06:52.545 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Buddy Cianci passed away this
morning in a Providence
hospital. He spent 21 years as

06:52.545 --> 06:56.916 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
mayor, helped revitalize the
city and gained national
attention, but ultimately went
to

06:56.916 --> 07:02.856 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
federal prison for corruption.
Buddy Cianci was 74 years old.

07:02.856 --> 07:08.094 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Wall Street gained ground for a
change today, as oil prices
climbed again. The Dow Jones

07:08.094 --> 07:15.168 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
industrial average was up 125
points to close near 16070. The
Nasdaq rose 38 points, and

07:15.168 --> 07:19.539 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the S&amp;P 500 added 10.

07:19.539 --> 07:26.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It turns out Hawaii and Alaska
are the places to be for your
own well-being. An annual
Gallup/Healthways

07:26.713 --> 07:33.186 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
survey of all 50 states finds
Hawaii is number one when it
comes to a sense of well-being

07:33.186 --> 07:39.893 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for the fifth time since 2008.
Alaska is second, after coming
in first last year, and is
followed

07:39.893 --> 07:44.998 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by Montana, Colorado, and
Wyoming. And at the bottom, West
Virginia has the lowest ranking

07:44.998 --> 07:48.201 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for the seventh straight year.

07:48.201 --> 07:54.074 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, finally, new times in toy
land. Mattel announced today
that Barbie dolls will now

07:54.074 --> 08:01.948 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be sold in three body types,
curvy, tall and petite, plus new
skin tones and hair styles,

08:01.948 --> 08:07.420 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to reflect a more diverse view
of beauty. And LEGO confirmed
there's a figure in a wheelchair

08:07.420 --> 08:13.526 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in an upcoming set. It's the
company's first depiction of
disabilities ever.

08:13.526 --> 08:17.964 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
what you need to know about the
rapidly spreading Zika

08:17.964 --> 08:24.671 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
virus; an American student freed
from an Iranian prison speaks
out; when corn becomes
political,

08:24.671 --> 08:43.556 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the ethanol debate ahead of the
Iowa caucuses; and much more.

08:43.556 --> 08:49.062 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Just weeks ago, hardly anyone in
the U.S. knew what the Zika
virus was, much less worried

08:49.062 --> 08:54.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
about it. But the World Health
Organization's warning today put
the Americas, including

08:54.267 --> 08:59.773 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the U.S., on new notice. And,
suddenly, a mosquito-borne virus
is raising serious fears,

08:59.773 --> 09:03.176 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
especially for pregnant women.

09:03.176 --> 09:08.081 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Dr. Anthony Fauci is with the
National Institutes of Health,
and he updated the situation
today.

09:08.081 --> 09:11.351 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He joins us now from
the NIH campus.

09:11.351 --> 09:13.953 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Welcome back to the
program, Dr. Fauci.

09:13.953 --> 09:17.290 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Just how high a level
of concern is there?

09:17.290 --> 09:18.258 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. ANTHONY FAUCI, Director,
National Institute of Allergy
and Infectious Diseases: Well,

09:18.258 --> 09:24.564 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we certainly are taking this
very seriously. This is a new
virus for the Western Hemisphere

09:24.564 --> 09:28.301 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and the Americas. And it's been
explosive in its outbreak in
South America and in the

09:28.301 --> 09:31.037 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Caribbean.

09:31.037 --> 09:36.810 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One of the issues that you
mentioned that's important is
that it is associated, at least

09:36.810 --> 09:42.949 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
temporally and geographically,
with a disturbing increase in
the incidence of a very serious

09:42.949 --> 09:48.721 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
complication of pregnancy, and
that is fetuses having what's
called microcephaly.

09:48.721 --> 09:54.861 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And microcephaly is a problem
with the brain where the skull
and the head is small, and

09:54.861 --> 09:58.798 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
there's a developmental problem
and/or a damage problem to the
brain, leading to dire
consequences,

09:58.798 --> 10:02.869 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
often death, but
major impairment.

10:02.869 --> 10:08.675 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Zika as a virus infection itself
is relatively mild, and that's
the reason why it's been

10:08.675 --> 10:14.147 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
essentially off the radar screen
of people until it came in with
a vengeance to South

10:14.147 --> 10:19.018 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
America. It causes a mild
illness that lasts anywhere from
three to five to seven days,

10:19.018 --> 10:22.021 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and then it goes away,
and you're fine.

10:22.021 --> 10:28.995 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's the potential complication
that we're seeing in South
America and in the Caribbean

10:28.995 --> 10:32.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with regard to pregnancy. And
it's interesting, because it's
an association that hasn't been

10:32.866 --> 10:36.769 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
completely proven to
be cause and effect.

10:36.769 --> 10:41.341 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It certainly is associated, and
it's puzzling, and we're trying
to figure out just what the

10:41.341 --> 10:46.613 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
nature of this association is
between infection and pregnant
women and this problem of
microcephaly

10:46.613 --> 10:48.481 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in the fetus and in the infant.

10:48.481 --> 10:52.318 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Is it understood
why this is spreading so fast?

10:52.318 --> 10:57.624 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. ANTHONY FAUCI: Well, one of
the reasons that we see spread
like this, Judy, is that,

10:57.624 --> 11:03.429 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
up until now, South America and
the Caribbean has been what we
call immunologically naive

11:03.429 --> 11:10.003 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to Zika virus. They have never
had Zika virus in the Western
Hemisphere or in the Americas.

11:10.003 --> 11:14.974 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so when a new infection like
this comes in, there's no
background immunity in the

11:14.974 --> 11:21.314 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
population that would blunt the
outbreak that we're seeing now,
whereas something like dengue

11:21.314 --> 11:26.386 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
infection has been prevalent in
South America, particularly in
Brazil, for several years

11:26.386 --> 11:32.025 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
now. So there's that background
immunity to it. No such immunity
with Zika.

11:32.025 --> 11:37.230 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's perfectly new to them,
which makes it much, much easier
to explode in the population.

11:37.230 --> 11:42.802 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That, together with the fact
that they're loaded with
mosquitoes, who are the vectors

11:42.802 --> 11:48.141 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
of this particular virus
infection. The Aedes aegypti
mosquitoes are all over South
America

11:48.141 --> 11:52.111 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and Brazil, and that's the
perfect vector to spread this
infection.

11:52.111 --> 11:56.182 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, we have
talked about pregnant women.
Should everyone be concerned?

11:56.182 --> 11:59.085 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Just women? I mean, who
should be most worried?

11:59.085 --> 12:03.656 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
DR. ANTHONY FAUCI: Well,
certainly the focus is on women
who are pregnant.

12:03.656 --> 12:08.995 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that is the reason why the
Centers for Disease Control and
Prevention, the CDC, has

12:08.995 --> 12:14.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
given a guideline travel alert
that, if an individual, a woman
is pregnant, planning

12:14.934 --> 12:19.105 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to be pregnant, not sure if
they're pregnant, they should
seriously consider postponing

12:19.105 --> 12:22.241 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
any travel to this region.

12:22.241 --> 12:28.047 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it is recommended that they
actually postpone until this
situation gets clarified because

12:28.047 --> 12:31.384 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of this association with
this dire consequence.

12:31.384 --> 12:36.189 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And what about
for men? I mean, for men who
contract the virus, can they can

12:36.189 --> 12:39.025 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they pass it onto a woman
through sexual contact?

12:39.025 --> 12:41.861 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
DR. ANTHONY FAUCI: Well,
that's a good question.

12:41.861 --> 12:45.999 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What has happened is, first of
all, for a man who has no issue
with passing it on to

12:45.999 --> 12:53.172 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a woman sexually, it's a mild
illness. But there is a single
case that has been reported

12:53.172 --> 12:59.345 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of a man who was infected in the
region, went home to his wife,
had sex with his wife, and

12:59.345 --> 13:03.383 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
she definitely got infected with
Zika, and she had never left the
country.

13:03.383 --> 13:11.190 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, that's one example. We don't
know if that's an outlier that's
a very rare event, or if

13:11.190 --> 13:16.863 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that is something that we will
see more commonly. And the way
you find out is do careful
following

13:16.863 --> 13:21.434 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and natural history studies and
case control studies. So we're
paying close attention to

13:21.434 --> 13:24.904 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that. We're not sure how
significant it's going to be.

13:24.904 --> 13:29.242 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But, as we
reported a minute ago, there's
no vaccine yet, no treatment.

13:29.242 --> 13:34.147 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. ANTHONY FAUCI: That is
correct. Vaccines under certain
circumstances such as this,

13:34.147 --> 13:40.553 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with a new virus and a new
disease, generally take a few
years before you have a vaccine

13:40.553 --> 13:45.158 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
that's approved by the
regulatory authorities and ready
to be distributed.

13:45.158 --> 13:50.463 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, we're not thinking about
that for at least another three
to five years. However, since

13:50.463 --> 13:56.002 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we have experience with similar
viruses, we are now in the
process of beginning the early

13:56.002 --> 14:03.276 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
stages of developing a vaccine
for a phase one trial to
determine safety and whether

14:03.276 --> 14:06.512 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
or not it induces the
proper immune response.

14:06.512 --> 14:11.150 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we fully expect that we will
be able to be into that phase
one trial within the calendar

14:11.150 --> 14:14.087 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
year of 2016.

14:14.087 --> 14:19.058 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And beyond that,
just warning people to stay away
from these affected areas.

14:19.058 --> 14:22.695 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. ANTHONY FAUCI: Well, that's
the truth. In other words, you
have got to be careful,

14:22.695 --> 14:25.998 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
particularly with pregnant
women, to make sure that if they
are pregnant, that they

14:25.998 --> 14:30.903 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
go by the CDC guidelines and, as
best as possible, avoid travel
to these areas.

14:30.903 --> 14:35.374 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Dr. Tony Fauci
at the NIH, we thank you.

14:35.374 --> 14:47.153 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
DR. ANTHONY FAUCI:
Good to be with you.

14:47.153 --> 14:53.860 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now we return to
the stories of the Americans
recently freed from detention

14:53.860 --> 14:59.098 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
in Iran, and turn to our
interview with one of those set
free on January 16.

14:59.098 --> 15:01.601 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
For that, we go to
Hari Sreenivasan.

15:01.601 --> 15:06.439 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: We heard for
the first time today from Jason
Rezaian, the Washington Post

15:06.439 --> 15:12.378 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
reporter released from more than
500 days' imprisonment by
Iranian authorities. He was

15:12.378 --> 15:16.048 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
part of a prisoner swap with
Iran that released four
Americans in exchange for
Iranians here

15:16.048 --> 15:17.884 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in the U.S.

15:17.884 --> 15:21.420 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Rezaian spoke at the
headquarters of the paper this
morning.

15:21.420 --> 15:24.924 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JASON REZAIAN, Journalist
Detained in Iran: For much of
the 18 months I was in prison,

15:24.924 --> 15:30.096 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
my Iranian interrogators told me
that The Washington Post didn't
exist, that no one

15:30.096 --> 15:38.037 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
knew of my plight, and that the
United States government
wouldn't lift a finger for my
release.

15:38.037 --> 15:43.543 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, I'm here in this room
with the very people who helped
prove the Iranians wrong

15:43.543 --> 15:46.212 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in so many ways.

15:46.212 --> 15:50.683 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: There was a
fifth American released from
prison in Iran, separate from

15:50.683 --> 15:54.887 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the deal that freed Rezaian and
three others. His name is
Matthew Trevithick, and he had

15:54.887 --> 15:59.325 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
been held for 40 days in
Tehran's notorious Evin prison.

15:59.325 --> 16:03.196 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Trevithick was in Tehran to
study Farsi when he was detained
late last year.

16:03.196 --> 16:05.898 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He joins me now from New York.

16:05.898 --> 16:09.502 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, why were you in prison?
What did the authorities say?

16:09.502 --> 16:15.374 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MATTHEW TREVITHICK, Freed From
Iranian Prison: So, I was
arrested and accused of trying
to

16:15.374 --> 16:22.315 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
overthrow the Iranian
government. And they said I had
access to bank accounts with
millions

16:22.315 --> 16:29.655 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of dollars in them, and that I
knew the locations of weapons
caches around the country.

16:29.655 --> 16:35.428 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And when I pointed out to them
that the only things I had in my
possession were Farsi textbooks,

16:35.428 --> 16:39.398 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a newspaper or two, some flash
cards and a pencil, well, they
weren't very happy to hear

16:39.398 --> 16:40.499 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
that.

16:40.499 --> 16:43.302 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Right. So what
happened? How were you arrested?

16:43.302 --> 16:48.307 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATTHEW TREVITHICK: On my way to
buy my plane ticket home, I had
just talked with my parents

16:48.307 --> 16:52.979 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the day before on Skype and
said, really looking to being
home -- really looking forward
to

16:52.979 --> 16:58.084 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
being home for Christmas and New
Year's, and I think my time here
is done. I have been

16:58.084 --> 17:02.688 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
here for just over three months.
And I have seen some things, and
it's time to come home.

17:02.688 --> 17:08.728 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The next morning, I was walking
outside of the dorm. It's a
student dorm at Tehran
University.

17:08.728 --> 17:14.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And just, you know, a few feet
from the front gate, three men
jumped out of a car, asked

17:14.300 --> 17:18.337 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
me one question,
"Matthew?" I said, "Yes."

17:18.337 --> 17:22.541 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they pushed me into the
backseat, and off we went to
Evin prison.

17:22.541 --> 17:24.043 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: When were the
conditions in that prison like?
What was the room you

17:24.043 --> 17:26.412 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
were staying in like?

17:26.412 --> 17:32.685 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MATTHEW TREVITHICK: I was in
solitary confinement for 29
days. And it's a very small
room. It's

17:32.685 --> 17:37.623 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
about six-feet-by-seven-feet, as
I measured it. And I'm just over
six feet tall myself,

17:37.623 --> 17:41.360 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
so this makes for a pretty
cramped -- pretty cramped
living.

17:41.360 --> 17:46.832 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's no bed. There's no
pillow. You know, it's a
concrete floor with a very thin
carpet

17:46.832 --> 17:53.172 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
over it that's been very worn.
And, you know, that feeling of
worn, of things being used

17:53.172 --> 17:57.810 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was very -- I mean, it was a
very consistent theme in my
time.

17:57.810 --> 18:03.382 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Inside the prison, you are very
well -- you're very aware that
you're in a place where a

18:03.382 --> 18:08.187 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
lot of people have been before
you, and most likely a lot of
people will be after you.

18:08.187 --> 18:11.457 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: You were in
solitary for that long. Did you
meet other prisoners in

18:11.457 --> 18:13.526 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the time that you were not,
and what were they in for?

18:13.526 --> 18:15.528 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MATTHEW TREVITHICK: I did.

18:15.528 --> 18:19.665 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When I started to cross paths
with other prisoners, I was
moved out of solitary
confinement at

18:19.665 --> 18:25.271 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the evening of day 29, and
stayed in what they referred to
as a suite -- I disagreed

18:25.271 --> 18:29.275 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with their terminology a bit --
where two other prisoners there
were, and they had seen

18:29.275 --> 18:32.712 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
other prisoners come
and go as well.

18:32.712 --> 18:37.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's, I think, when you
start to become more aware of
who you are sharing this
building

18:37.583 --> 18:41.988 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with. It was there that I
learned that Jason Rezaian was
downstairs. It was there that

18:41.988 --> 18:48.361 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I learned that newspaper
editors, journalists,
dissidents, artists, poets,
intellectuals,

18:48.361 --> 18:52.765 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
et cetera, were all
in the cells nearby.

18:52.765 --> 18:58.070 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, you know, that also -- you
draw a small amount of comfort
from knowing who you're

18:58.070 --> 19:00.840 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
sharing this building with.

19:00.840 --> 19:04.043 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: You know,
Jason Rezaian mentioned today
that he was constantly told

19:04.043 --> 19:08.147 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that the paper that he worked
for didn't exist, right?

19:08.147 --> 19:11.283 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When you're in solitary, you
obviously have no access to
information that the rest of

19:11.283 --> 19:15.788 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the world is trying to work on
behalf of you to try to get you
released. What kept you

19:15.788 --> 19:18.224 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
going through all this?

19:18.224 --> 19:21.660 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MATTHEW TREVITHICK: You know, in
fact, before I answer your
question, the very first
sentence

19:21.660 --> 19:27.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they said to me on day one, you
know, within an hour of being
taken off the street, my

19:27.233 --> 19:32.104 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
interrogators pacing the --
right behind me, and I'm facing
a wall and can't see his face.

19:32.104 --> 19:35.541 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And he says, "Do you know
who Jason Rezaian is?"

19:35.541 --> 19:39.578 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I said, "Of course. The whole
world knows that name." And he
said, next sentence, "He's

19:39.578 --> 19:42.448 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
never leaving, and
neither are you."

19:42.448 --> 19:49.255 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that was the tone by which
we started. That set the tone
for my time there.

19:49.255 --> 19:52.591 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: So, did you
imagine that the United States
government was working on

19:52.591 --> 19:54.293 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
your behalf or your parents?

19:54.293 --> 19:56.529 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MATTHEW TREVITHICK:
Yes, absolutely.

19:56.529 --> 20:01.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I had a very simple check-in
system with my mother every day.
We'd shoot each other a

20:01.467 --> 20:04.837 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
text note, and say, hi, Matt.
How is everything? Hi, mom,
everything is going really well.

20:04.837 --> 20:08.441 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Thanks. Or everything
is going fine. Thanks.

20:08.441 --> 20:15.414 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think when I started to
not reply to those messages, she
got a little more concerned.

20:15.414 --> 20:21.420 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then something very bizarre
happened. On day three, they
hand me my phone, and they

20:21.420 --> 20:24.857 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
said, we want you to call your
mother. And they had prepared a
very stilted script that

20:24.857 --> 20:28.694 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
I had to kind of
regurgitate from memory.

20:28.694 --> 20:32.765 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they said, call your mother
and tell her you're going to the
mountains for a while

20:32.765 --> 20:38.904 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
and will not be in
communication. And, of course,
calling a mother and trying to
say

20:38.904 --> 20:41.040 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
everything is fine when it's not
fine, I don't think that ever
works.

20:41.040 --> 20:43.242 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Right.

20:43.242 --> 20:48.447 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATTHEW TREVITHICK: And -- but,
no, I mean, to answer your
question, you know, in my time

20:48.447 --> 20:54.153 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
overseas in the Middle East and
Central Asia, you know, you
start to become aware of just

20:54.153 --> 21:02.328 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
how hard so many people work the
minute an American goes missing
anywhere.

21:02.328 --> 21:07.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I spent time in the cell
wondering who got my file on
Christmas and who got my file

21:07.900 --> 21:10.703 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on New Year's, and I kind of
felt a little guilty about that.

21:10.703 --> 21:14.273 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Hey, you sent
out a tweet today that I wanted
a little explanation of.

21:14.273 --> 21:18.444 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It says basically this photo
sums up your entire feelings
about Iran. It was a -- tell

21:18.444 --> 21:21.580 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
me what, does that mean?

21:21.580 --> 21:27.953 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATTHEW TREVITHICK: So, it's a
photo. I'm at the Golestan
Palace in Tehran. And the

21:27.953 --> 21:36.896 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
backdrop of the photograph is
beautiful Persian artwork, you
know, traditional mosaic tiling.

21:36.896 --> 21:44.069 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's absolutely captivating.
And, you know, so in one sense,
that, you know, deep

21:44.069 --> 21:52.077 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
beauty and sort of romance is --
of the culture is demonstrated
in the photograph. And then

21:52.077 --> 21:56.815 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on one side of the photograph,
my friend who took the picture
just managed to capture the

21:56.815 --> 22:01.020 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
fact that, you know, somebody in
uniform was watching me as I
posed and smiled for the

22:01.020 --> 22:03.522 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
picture.

22:03.522 --> 22:11.964 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I just think that that sense
of always being watched and
always being under surveillance

22:11.964 --> 22:17.169 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is what some Iranians live with
and it's what all foreigners
know is happening. And, you

22:17.169 --> 22:19.972 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
know, you do -- you hope to deal
with one more than the other.

22:19.972 --> 22:23.742 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Finally, you
have worked in Afghanistan for a
number of years. You

22:23.742 --> 22:28.214 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have lived in Turkey. This is
part of your life's work. Do you
plan to go back to the

22:28.214 --> 22:30.516 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
region? What are
your plans next?

22:30.516 --> 22:32.384 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATTHEW TREVITHICK: I will
certainly be heading back, but I
think Iran and I have had enough

22:32.384 --> 22:34.253 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
for now.

22:34.253 --> 22:37.223 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All right,
Matthew, thanks so much for
joining us.

22:37.223 --> 22:46.532 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MATTHEW TREVITHICK:
Absolutely. Thank you.

